---
description: Project-wide conventions for the Cafe Management System
alwaysApply: true
---

The full project guide lives in [AGENTS.md](mdc:AGENTS.md). Read it before
suggesting non-trivial changes — Next.js 16, `@supabase/ssr`, and Tailwind
v4 all have conventions that differ from older versions.

Quick reference:

- Routes: role-based route groups under `src/app/` (`(pos)`, `(inventory)`,
  `(branch)`, `(admin)`, `(auth)`).
- Supabase: import `createClient` from
  [`@/lib/supabase/server`](mdc:src/lib/supabase/server.ts) on the server,
  [`@/lib/supabase/client`](mdc:src/lib/supabase/client.ts) in the browser,
  and [`@/lib/supabase/admin`](mdc:src/lib/supabase/admin.ts) only when you
  need to bypass RLS from a trusted server context.
- Session refresh runs in [`src/proxy.ts`](mdc:src/proxy.ts) (Next.js 16
  renamed `middleware.ts` to `proxy.ts`). Don't add a second one.
- Env vars go through [`@/lib/env`](mdc:src/lib/env.ts) and must be added
  to [`.env.example`](mdc:.env.example) in the same change.
- Styling uses Tailwind v4 design tokens defined in
  [`globals.css`](mdc:src/app/globals.css). Prefer `bg-surface`,
  `text-foreground-muted`, the `wood-*` scale, and `accent` over raw
  colors.
- Naming: folders / component files / routes are `kebab-case`; React
  components and types are `PascalCase`; hooks are `useCamelCase`;
  variables and functions are `camelCase`; module constants are
  `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE`; Postgres tables/columns are `snake_case` (plural
  tables, singular columns, foreign keys as `<table_singular>_id`).
  Full table in [README](mdc:README.md#naming-conventions).
- Commits: Conventional Commits (`<type>(<scope>): <subject>`,
  imperative, lowercase, no period). Allowed types: `feat`, `fix`,
  `refactor`, `perf`, `docs`, `test`, `build`, `ci`, `chore`, `style`,
  `revert`. Branches: `<type>/<short-kebab-description>`. Only commit
  when the user explicitly asks. Full guide in
  [README](mdc:README.md#commits-and-branches).
